<TITLE> Friendship Cup postponed after Sidr </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 18 (bdnews24.com) - The Friendship Cup football tournament has been postponed temporarily in the aftermath of cyclone Sidr, which ravaged the south west coast Thursday night. The Friendship Cup, with Malaysian Perak FC, Nepalese Friends Club, Kolkata's Mohammedan, Dhaka Mohammedan and Abahani Limited, was scheduled for Nov 28 to December 10 at Bangabandhu National Stadium. Army chief General Moeen U Ahmed, who is the chairman of the National Sports Council, directed the committee to suspend the tournament after a meeting with the organising committee, according to a press release Sunday. The release said fresh dates for the Friendship Cup would be announced at a later date. The army chief who is also chairman of the tournament advisory committee, and the organising committee called upon everyone including organisers, club officials, players and coaches to extend help to the survivors of cyclone Sidr. bdn
